                <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none">
                    <div class="highlight-box rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
                        <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-blue-300">Chapter Overview</h4>
                        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
                            Understanding computer architecture is essential for malware analysis, reverse engineering, and 
                            understanding hardware-based attacks. We examine the von Neumann architecture, instruction set 
                            architectures, and the microarchitectural features that impact security.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <h4 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-300 mt-8 mb-4">1.2.1 The Von Neumann Architecture</h4>

                    <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                        Proposed by John von Neumann in 1945, this stored-program architecture remains the foundation of modern 
                        computing. Its core principle: both data and instructions reside in the same memory space, fetched and 
                        executed by a central processing unit.
                    </p>

                    <div class="network-diagram rounded-xl p-8 my-8 border border-blue-500/30">
