                    </div>

                    <h4 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-300 mt-8 mb-4">1.2.2 CPU Components & Execution Cycle</h4>

                    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-6">
                        <div class="detail-box rounded-lg p-6">
                            <h5 class="font-semibold text-blue-300 mb-4">Control Unit (CU)</h5>
                            <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-300 text-sm">
                                <li>• <strong>Program Counter (PC):</strong> Holds address of next instruction</li>
                                <li>• <strong>Instruction Register (IR):</strong> Holds current instruction</li>
                                <li>• <strong>Instruction Decoder:</strong> Translates opcode to control signals</li>
                                <li>• <strong>Timing & Control Logic:</strong> Orchestrates execution phases</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="detail-box rounded-lg p-6">
                            <h5 class="font-semibold text-blue-300 mb-4">Arithmetic Logic Unit (ALU)</h5>
                            <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-300 text-sm">
                                <li>• <strong>Integer Operations:</strong> ADD, SUB, MUL, DIV</li>
                                <li>• <strong>Bitwise Operations:</strong> AND, OR, XOR, NOT, shifts</li>
                                <li>• <strong>Comparison:</strong> Sets flags (Zero, Negative, Carry, Overflow)</li>
                                <li>• <strong>FPU (optional):</strong> Floating-point operations</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="detail-box rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
                        <h5 class="font-semibold text-blue-300 mb-4">The Instruction Cycle (Fetch-Decode-Execute)</h5>
                        <div class="space-y-4">
                            <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                                <div class="layer-indicator bg-blue-600 text-white flex-shrink-0">1</div>
                                <div>
                                    <h6 class="font-semibold text-slate-200">Fetch</h6>
                                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">PC → Address Bus → Memory returns instruction → IR. PC incremented by instruction length.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                                <div class="layer-indicator bg-blue-600 text-white flex-shrink-0">2</div>
                                <div>
                                    <h6 class="font-semibold text-slate-200">Decode</h6>
                                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Opcode extracted from IR. Control unit generates signals for ALU, registers, memory.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                                <div class="layer-indicator bg-blue-600 text-white flex-shrink-0">3</div>
                                <div>
                                    <h6 class="font-semibold text-slate-200">Execute</h6>
                                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">ALU performs operation or data moved between registers/memory. Status flags updated.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                                <div class="layer-indicator bg-blue-600 text-white flex-shrink-0">4</div>
                                <div>
                                    <h6 class="font-semibold text-slate-200">Writeback</h6>
                                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Results stored to destination register or memory location.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <h4 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-300 mt-8 mb-4">1.2.3 Instruction Set Architectures (ISA)</h4>

                    <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                        The ISA defines the interface between software and hardware. Security professionals encounter multiple ISAs 
                        during malware analysis (x86 for Windows malware, ARM for mobile/IoT, MIPS for embedded devices).
                    </p>

                    <div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
                        <table class="w-full text-sm text-left text-slate-300">
                            <thead class="text-xs text-slate-400 uppercase bg-slate-800">
