                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 bg-yellow-900/20 border border-yellow-500/30 rounded-lg">
                                <span class="font-semibold text-yellow-300">L2 Cache (Unified)</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">~10ns | 256KB-1MB per core</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 bg-green-900/20 border border-green-500/30 rounded-lg">
                                <span class="font-semibold text-green-300">L3 Cache (Shared)</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">~20-50ns | 8-64MB shared</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 bg-blue-900/20 border border-blue-500/30 rounded-lg">
                                <span class="font-semibold text-blue-300">Main Memory (RAM)</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">~100ns | 8-512GB</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 bg-purple-900/20 border border-purple-500/30 rounded-lg">
                                <span class="font-semibold text-purple-300">Storage (SSD/HDD)</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">~10μs-10ms | 256GB-10TB+</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="detail-box rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
                        <h5 class="font-semibold text-blue-300 mb-3">Cache Side-Channel Attacks</h5>
                        <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4">
                            The timing difference between cache hits and misses creates information leakage. Attackers can infer 
                            secret data by monitoring cache access patterns.
                        </p>
                        <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-300 text-sm">
                            <li>• <strong>Flush+Reload:</strong> Attacker flushes cache line, victim accesses data, attacker measures reload time</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Prime+Probe:</strong> Attacker fills cache set, victim evicts entries, attacker detects which lines were accessed</li>
                            <li>• <strong>Spectre/Meltdown:</strong> Exploit speculative execution and cache timing to read arbitrary memory</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-slate-400 text-xs mt-4">
                            Mitigations: Cache partitioning, constant-time algorithms, speculative execution barriers (lfence)
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="highlight-box rounded-xl p-6 mt-8">
