                            <p class="text-slate-500">----------------</p>
                            <p class="text-slate-400">Low Addresses (Stack grows down)</p>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm">
                            Without NX: Attacker injects shellcode onto stack, overwrites return address to jump to it.<br>
                            With NX: Return-Oriented Programming (ROP) chains together existing code fragments (gadgets).
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <h4 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-300 mt-8 mb-4">1.3.4 Heap Memory & Dynamic Allocation</h4>

                    <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
