                                    <h6 class="font-semibold text-slate-200">Twisted Pair Copper (UTP/STP)</h6>
                                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 mt-2">
                                        Pairs twisted to reduce electromagnetic interference (crosstalk). Categories define 
                                        bandwidth and shielding:
                                    </p>
                                    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-2 mt-2 text-xs">
                                        <div class="bg-slate-800 p-2 rounded">Cat 5e: 100MHz, 1Gbps</div>
                                        <div class="bg-slate-800 p-2 rounded">Cat 6: 250MHz, 10Gbps (55m)</div>
                                        <div class="bg-slate-800 p-2 rounded">Cat 6a: 500MHz, 10Gbps (100m)</div>
                                        <div class="bg-slate-800 p-2 rounded">Cat 8: 2000MHz, 40Gbps (30m)</div>
                                    </div>
                                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-2">
                                        <strong>Security:</strong> TEMPEST attacks (electromagnetic emanations), wiretapping, 
                                        port security (MAC limiting)
                                    </p>
                                </div>

                                <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
                                    <h6 class="font-semibold text-slate-200">Fiber Optic (Single/Multi-mode)</h6>
